{"id": "554", "instruction": "We now define an algorithm: The definition of a(n) is the number of digits in n! (n factorial) excluding any trailing zeros in its decimal representation. Given the input x_list (a series of values): [67, 68, 69, 70, 71, 72, 73, 74, 75, 76], determine the corresponding output sequence y_list.\n\nOptions:\nA. [82, 83, 86, 87, 87, 89, 91, 93, 93, 95]\nB. [81, 82, 85, 85, 87, 89, 90, 92, 92, 94]\nC. [79, 81, 83, 84, 85, 87, 89, 91, 91, 93]\nD. [77, 80, 82, 84, 85, 87, 89, 91, 91, 93]\nE. [80, 82, 84, 84, 86, 88, 89, 92, 93, 94]\nF. [80, 81, 83, 86, 86, 88, 90, 92, 93, 94]\nG. [80, 82, 84, 85, 86, 88, 90, 92, 92, 94]\nH. [78, 80, 82, 83, 84, 86, 88, 90, 90, 92]\nI. [79, 83, 84, 86, 87, 88, 90, 92, 92, 95]\nJ. [81, 83, 85, 86, 87, 89, 91, 93, 93, 95]", "output": "G"}
